James Edward CLAYTON, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. Clarence JONES, Sheriff, Dallas County, Defendant-Appellee. No. 73-2574. United States Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Nov. 7, 1973. James Edward Clayton, pro se. John B. Tolle, Asst. Dist. Atty., Dallas, Tex., for defendant-appellee.

Before THORNBERRY, GOLDBERG and RONEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

The appeal is ordered dismissed for want of prosecution for appellant’s failure to file a brief within the time fixed by the rules. Rule 9(b). See Tidwell v. Dees, 5th Cir. 1972, 464 F.2d 1297.
